properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 18 at 11:38AM CST until January 18 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Sioux Falls SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Winter Weather Advisory, blowing snow. Winds
gusting as high as 45 mph. For the Wind Chill Advisory, very
cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as 30 below zero.

* WHERE...Portions of central, east central, south central and
southeast South Dakota.

* WHEN...For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 6 PM CST this
evening. For the Wind Chill Advisory, from 6 PM this evening
to noon CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility. The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas.

Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
